{{notability|date=October 2011}} {{Infobox holiday |holiday_name = Fossil Fools Day |type = |image = |imagesize = |caption = |official_name = |nickname = |observedby = |litcolor = |longtype = |significance = |begins = |ends = |date =1 April |scheduling = same day each year |duration = 1 day |frequency = annual |celebrations = |observances = |relatedto = }}
'''Fossil Fools Day''' is an environmental demonstration day. It occurs on April 1. The name is a play on the term [[fossil fuel]]s and [[April Fools' Day]].
Fossil Fools Day began in 2004 with coordinated actions across the United States and Canada.<ref>Kim Teplitzky (October 25, 2004), “Declaring Independence from Dirty Energy.” Wiretap Magazine. {{cite web |url=http://www.wiretapmag.org/stories/20291 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-01-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081029000950/http://www.wiretapmag.org/stories/20291/ |archivedate=2008-10-29 |df= }}</ref> Subsequent Fossil Fools Days have been held in many cities around the world, and are generally organized by one or more environmental organizations with funding from [[Energy Action Coalition]] and [[Rising Tide North America|Rising Tide]].<ref>[http://energyactioncoalition.org/whatwedo Energy Action: What we do]</ref><ref>[http://www.fossilfoolsdayofaction.org/2009/ Fossil Fools Day 2009], [https://web.archive.org/web/20110726063356/http://www.fossilfoolsdayofaction.org/2009/ archived] at the Internet Archive, July 26, 2011.</ref><ref>"Don't be 'fossil fools' on April 1st urge Rising Tide campaigners", ''Leamington Spa Courier'', March 27, 2008, [http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-177153118.html online] at Highbeam (subscription required).</ref><ref>Sandy Cullen, "Tires 'Fossil Fools' Targets More than 100 Vehicles in Madison Had Tires Deflated in What Some Call 'Eco-Terrorism'", ''The Wisconsin State Journal'', April 2, 2008, [http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-177397917.html online at Highbeam], (subscription required).</ref><ref>Jay Fletcher, [http://www.greenleft.org.au/node/39327 "First Fossil Fools' Day in Australia"], Green Left, April 5, 2008.</ref><ref>Beth Daley, [http://www.boston.com/lifestyle/green/greenblog/2009/04/clean_coal_april_fools_says_gr_1.html "Clean coal? April Fools says Greenpeace"], The Green Blog, Boston.com, April 1, 2009.</ref><ref>James Chapman and Rebecca English, "The Obama show comes to town; First stop the Palace for tea with the Queen", ''[[The Daily Mail]]'', April 1, 2009, [http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-196905947.html online] at Highbeam (subscription required): "Fossil Fool's Day demonstration - environment campaigners wearing white will bring a huge block of ice to the ExCel centre".</ref><ref>[http://risingtidenorthamerica.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/FossilFoolsDay2010_RTNA.pdf Fossil Fools Day, April 1, 2010], Rising Tide North America (pdf)</ref><ref>Leah Gillen, [http://www.collegian.psu.edu/archive/2010/04/02/fossil_fools_day_brings_protes.aspx "Fossil Fools day brings protesters"], ''The Daily Collegian'', [[Pennsylvania State University]], April 2, 2010.</ref> These events oppose energy derived from fossil fuels, promote education about alternative sources of energy, and encourage support for [[climate justice]], strong legislation, corporate responsibility and a clean renewable energy future.
